cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper focuses on enhancing communication efficiency and quality on vehicular networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper analyzes a taxi GPS dataset and proposes clustering and information source selection algorithms, which are related to social and information networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The traffic allocation optimization model proposed in the paper can be considered as a control system, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - While the paper does not explicitly mention security, the communication model and algorithms proposed in the paper can have implications for security in vehicular networks. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses complex network theory to analyze and optimize information dissemination over vehicular networks, which falls under the scope of information theory.
